Wright County Sheriff's Office
September 3 at 3:26 PM ·

A Message to Parents Who Will Be Driving Their Children to School

Most schools in Wright County will be opening in the coming days and school districts are providing advice to parents who will choose to drop off and pick up their children from school. The expectation is that vehicle traffic will dramatically increase, causing delays that parents should be aware of and prepared for. To see the statement, click here:
http://www.co.wright.mn.us/CivicAlerts.aspx?AID=1908

On Friday, March 27, the ISD 876 School Board voted to cancel the proposed bond referendum scheduled for Tuesday, May 12, 2020 and postpone it to a later date. This incredibly difficult decision was made with the wellbeing of our students, staff, families, and residents in mind.

In light of several recent developments related to the COVID-19 (coronavirus) pandemic, including Governor Walz’ decision to extend school closures, our District is confident that postponing the referendum is what’s best to support our communities. To read the full announcement, visit https://www.cardinalstrong.org/

shared_text:
Billy D's Crooked Tavern
March 15 at 1:50 PM ·

Dear family and friends. We at Billy's are appreciative of your wonderful patronage over the last 13 months. We'd like to give back to those families with school age children during the governor's required school closings.

Starting tomorrow, if you have a child in school that is in need of a nutritious lunch, please stop in to Billy D's. We will provide you with a turkey sandwich, potato chips, and yogurt.....free of charge. We are not immune to the effects this school closing could have on families as we have young ones as well. Please let us be a part of your success with the kids at home in the coming weeks, as you've been vital to ours!

Thank you, and we hope to see you soon!

JOB OPENING ANNANDALE PUBLIC SCHOOLS

Special Education Paraprofessional - Elementary School
Under the direction of the Principal, the Special Education Paraprofessional is responsible for working with students with disabilities in meeting the academic, behavioral, emotional, social and physical needs as identified in the goals and supports of services of the IEP. Supports occur in either an individual or small group setting under the guidance of the special education or classroom teacher. This particular position is specifically for one on one support for a visually impaired student.

For a more detailed job description and instructions to apply, please visit the following link:

https://www.isd876.org/cms/lib/MN02201341/Centricity/Domain/22/Copy%20of%20Special%20Education%20Paraprofessional%20Job%20Posting%20-%20Visually%20Impaired%20.pdf

Night Custodian - High School

Under the direction of the Head Custodian, the Custodian performs environmental service tasks, cleaning and maintenance of school buildings, minor mechanical repairs, and support services for day and evening school activities. post_text:
With dangerously cold weather forecasted, it has been determined that the Annandale Schools will be closed for both Tuesday, January 29th and Wednesday, January 30th, 2019. This includes all programs and activities for Tuesday and Wednesday evenings. This decision was made now to ensure the safety of families, students, and staff and allow for adequate time for families to plan for the next two days.

Please note the following:

Cardinal Kid's Club will be contacting currently enrolled families with child care options and information.

The high school registration conferences scheduled for tonight(Monday) will take place as scheduled.

The high school band concert scheduled for tonight(Monday) will take place as scheduled.

The Alpine Ski meet will take place tonight(Monday) as scheduled.

Thank you,

Tim Prom
Superintendent, Annandale Schools
